In contrast to a fabulous bright kitchen - BLACK kitchens are a chic alternative!

Thank you @kmulvs for including me in your recent story on 'The Best Kitchen Paint Colors For 2023, According to Designers' for @elledecor!

..."Kitchens are increasingly becoming extensions of entertaining spaces,” New York City–based designer Phillip Thomas points out. “They need a glam backdrop!”
For the perfect dose of goes-with-anything-glamour, Thomas reaches for black, a shade that’s equal parts practical and pretty. “[It’s] particularly fabulous in a smaller kitchen, and while most people would shy away from a dark color in a smaller space, I find it tricks the eye into making the space feel larger,” he shares.

📷: @themichaelmundy

It has been a while and we all know I love a theme....

Let's discuss animal prints.... I LOVE animal prints! Tiger, zebra, leopard - oh my! Animal prints add timeless glamour that work in both traditional and modern settings. They work in colorful or neutral spaces. They add pattern and texture.
Layer animal printed rugs, velvet printed pillows, spotted wall coverings - the possibilities are endless.
A little goes a long way in upping the chic factor in any space!

Follow along as I highlight some of my favorite ways to use animal prints....

Animal Prints - Day 1

The fabulously talented @alexahamptoninc designed this knockout hand-painted tiger print wallpaper with @graciestudio for the @flowermagazine Showhouse!

Butler's Pantry, Scullery, Back Kitchen - call it what you may, that extra room in a home that could be used for food prep and clean up, keeping your china, serving pieces, vases, silver, small appliances, etc... is all the rage!! 

I love the history of the butler's pantries in the old, large estates .... typically, the butler was responsible for managing and locking the butler’s pantry at the end of the day. In some homes, the butler slept inside this room in case someone attempted to break in and steal family heirlooms - hence the name.  Today, a modern version of the butler's pantry is on the rise and I am frequently asked to incorporate these functional rooms into projects for my clients. Although fabulous, it needn't be a large room with all of the bells and whistles - a smaller, customized closet could do just fine depending on your needs.  Whether you love to entertain or simply love to collect beautiful pieces for your table, the extra space is always appreciated. Let’s do a week of butler's pantries for inspiration!! 

Butler's Pantries - Day 1

Blue lacquer butler pantry perfection in this Newport, RI project by the amazing @sommersruthie ! 

📷: @williamwaldronphoto

#butlerspantry #ruthiesommers #ptinc #butler #storage #kitchencloset #scullery #backkitchen #interiordesign #china #tabletop #vase #silver #heirloom #phillipthomasinteriors #design #kitchendesign

Butler's Pantries - Day 2

A butler’s pantry for EVERYTHING by @stephanielyntonhome home via @flowermagazine!!

Welcome to the “Colonel’s Cabinet of Curiosities”!

We have the honor of designing this year's Collectors Lounge in the Colonel's Room at the Park Avenue Armory in New York City for this year's Salon Art + Design Fair!
The space is filled with prized objects, art, and furniture from around the globe and spanning decades from Salon exhibitors Maison Gerard, Donzella, Lobel Modern NYC, Galerie Negropontes, Achille Salvagni Atelier, Liz O’Brien, and J. Loehmann Gallery among others with artistic creations by Andrew Tedesco Studios, Inc and Phillip Bland. We hope to transport you into a Baroque art gallery the moment you step within, illustrating the concept of your home as a work of art.

Follow along our stories this week as we transform this beautiful space.  And please do stop in and say hello when you visit Salon from November 9th-13th.
We can't wait to show you what we have created!
